OL,3,CCalls for changes to Jersey's complex
OL,4,Cplanning system
OL,6,FBuilders argue that restrictions
OL,7,Fparticularly jeopardise the
OL,8,Fdevelopment of vital affordable
OL,9,Fhousing projects.
OL,11,FBen Cairney, a construction firm
OL,12,Fdirector, says that whilst access to
OL,13,Fplanning officers has improved in
OL,14,Frecent years, the system itself is
OL,15,Fstill failing.
OL,17,FHe says: "The problem is the amount of
OL,18,Fred tape you've got to work your way
OL,19,Fthrough before, during, and after you
OL,20,Fget planning permission.
